---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import portrait from '../assets/martin-opedal.jpg';
---
<section id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">Profile</span>
    <h2>About</h2>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <Image
        src={portrait}
        alt="Portrait of Martin Opedal, Lead Cloud Solution Architect at Microsoft"
        widths={[200, 320, 400]}
        sizes="(min-width: 768px) 220px, 160px"
        class="about-photo"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
      />
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>
          I've been working with Azure since the platform launched. I spent the
          next decade running datacenter operations and cloud migrations side by
          side at Teknograd and Advania. Most of my landing zone opinions trace
          back to something that failed in physical infrastructure or broke in an
          ExpressRoute config.
        </p>
        <p>
          Now I architect Azure Landing Zones, AKS Automatic, and AI Foundry
          deployments for Nordic enterprises. I use Terraform daily. The modules
          I ship come from real customer engagements, not theory.
        </p>
        <p>
          I co-founded two craft breweries. Fermentation and infrastructure both
          need the right controls and patience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
